     <div type="commendation">
   <head>In commendation of the Author.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>NOT boldest blouds alone, wher guide is gone,</l>
      <l>Doth shew the brauest brag vppon their foe,</l>
      <l>Vnlesse that Art and rule, doth lead them on,</l>
      <l>As by a fine forecast, the charge must goe.</l>
      <l>For head withouten heed, still chops vppō il chance:</l>
      <l>&amp; cōduct is the ka<gap reason="illegible" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>e, that doth the charge aduāce<gap reason="illegible" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>
      </l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Reade Rich, a booke enricht with goodly store,</l>
      <l>VVher nought that worthy war can wish doth want,</l>
      <l>Eche stratagem so stately set, thou needst no more,</l>
      <l>Rich hath enricht his woork as naught is skant.</l>
      <l>Let Langius lye▪ and Machauel go make his mone:</l>
      <l>Mars and Bellona bids thee reade but Rich alone.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>G. Argal.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
